# Module Federation Conventions

- Remote apps expose modules; the dashboard consumes them via the `remotes` map in
  `apps/dashboard/vite.config.ts`. When adding a new exposed module or remote entry,
  update both the exposing app's federation config and the dashboard's `remotes` map.
- `react` and `react-dom` are shared as singletons across federation boundaries — do
  not introduce a second copy or a conflicting version range in any app's
  `shared` config without checking every other app.
- Federated modules load from `http://localhost:<port>/remoteEntry.js` in dev. Don't
  hardcode these URLs outside vite config; keep ports consistent with the table in
  `README.md`:
  - dashboard (host): 5173
  - prompt-manager: 5174
  - guardrail: 5175
  - user-manager: 5176
  - usages-data: 5177
- Be cautious with global/shared state across federation boundaries — each remote is
  a separately bundled app and can't assume in-memory state from another remote.
- When scaffolding a new remote app, mirror the existing `vite.config.ts` federation
  block (name, exposes, shared react/react-dom singletons) and wire it into the
  dashboard's `remotes` map before considering the app "integrated."
